Use of the Duostock eliminates the necessity for the shooter to bring the head down to the rifle, as proper placement will assure an immediate and constant cheek weld while keeping the head upright. With a standard stock the shooter would need to place the high in the pocket in order to maintain this kind of shooting posture.

The Duostock consists of upper and lower surface areas for the absorption of recoil. All of this makes for a more stable, consistent shooting platform that puts optics or iron sights in direct alignment with the shooters eye, resulting in increased comfort, speed and accuracy. title: For Sale:  Heckler & Koch P7M8   H&K P7 M8
postcontent: Heckler & Koch P7M8 is the perfect auto-loading police-use pistol. The reason it is considered ideal is due to its completely unique safety system, namely the "squeezecocker" control surface built into the front of the grip. When the operator picks up the firearm, the main shooting hand instinctually squeezes the panel rearward, and this action cocks the striker rearward while unlocking the sear for use. The panel is spring-loaded, which means when pressure is reduced, it snaps forward, decocking the striker and locking the trigger. This system is also designed to release the slide when it is locked rearward. This design eliminates the need for a decocker, external safety lever or slide stop lever, making the sides of the firearm completely flush and reducing overall width. The barrel is fixed (does not cant upwards) which means despite the firearm's compact size, it is capable of printing groups of 2 inches or less at 25 yards. This accuracy is easily comparable to many high-end automatic pistols in production.  It has classic three white-dot sights dovetailed into the slide. I purchased it New in 1996 and have fired approximately 400 rounds through it without a single jam.Will include extra mags and nice holster.OREGON Residents ONLY

postcontent:
Utah and Oregon Concealed Carry Class
Saturday, June 7, 2014 10:00 AM
Portland Small Circle Jujitsu, 4030 NE Broadway St, Potland, OR 97232
Class cost is $65. Save $5 by pre-registering online!
Pre-Register Online: http://www.keepcalmandcarry.net/utah-and-oregon-concealed-carry-class-7-6-2014-Registration

This class covers everything you need to get your Oregon Concealed Handgun License and your Utah Concealed Firearms Permit.

Our course exceeds all firearms safety training exceeds the requirements to obtain your Utah CFP, pursuant to Utah Code Title 53 Chapter 5 Section 704, and your Oregon CHL pursuant to ORS 166.291(f)(G).

Our process starts with issuing you a packet of information, an application for your permit, and fingerprint cards that you will need. We will do your fingerprinting, take your passport photo and make copies of your driver's license before class starts. We do this so that upon completion of this class, you will have a complete packet which you can submit to Utah BCI (Bureau of Criminal Identification) with your payment. You will also have all the information you need to obtain your Oregon CHL from your local Sheriff's department.

Subjects covered are: Basic Handgun Safety, Tactical Issues, Concealed Carry Firearm selection tips, Ammunition, Holsters, Gun Free Zones, Reciprocity, Cleaning, Storage, Firearm Transport, Justifiable Force, Criminal and Civil liability, How to interact with Law Enforcement, and how to apply for your Permit.

After attending this class you will have a fundamental understanding about handgun safety and the rights and responsibilities and laws associated with the carrying of a concealed Handgun in multiple states.

This is NOT a live firing class. Do NOT bring a firearm with you to the class.

Even though the class time is only scheduled to be 2 1/2 hours long, there will be time for questions and answers after the class.

More Information: http://www.keepcalmandcarry.net/utah-and-oregon-concealed-carry-class-7-6-2014-Schedule

Developed from the operational experience of the Magpul DynamicsSM team, the B.A.D. Lever (Battery Assist Device) is designed to considerably improve the speed and efficiency of the AR15/M16 bolt catch. The B.A.D.
